Celebrating Guru Gobind Singh ji’s Spiritual, Heroic, Victorious, Impactful Life 🙏🙏 
His words translated for many to understand:
“Dear God, grant my request so that I may never deviate from doing good deeds. That, I shall have no fear of the enemy when I go into battle and with determination I will be victorious. He fought for the right of freedom for all, sacrificed his 4 sons, father, mother and himself! 
He is the founder of Khalsa 🙏
He was a true “Sant Sipahi” Spiritual Warrior! - our Guru 🙏🙏🙏🙏

From a small town Punjabi girl in Rajasthan to becoming an engineer with U.S Airforce! Very inspiring story of Manveer motivates young generation and parents for making sure kids are getting educated. She won the title for Mrs. Punjabi Punjaban USA - 2nd runner up.
We had tears I or eyes filming her heart felt interview.
She hails from Rajasthan, talks about the tough time her family had to provide for her fees.
She was determined to get educated, and got her degree in engineering from the U.S.A and worked as an engineer in U.S Force. Commendable! Sunny Babbar also was emotional remembering the courage of his mother while talking to Manveer Brar!
She won the title of Mrs. Punjaban USA - 2nd runner up. We are so proud of her. @noorie_brar @gigipanwar

Proud of Mandeep Brar, Mrs. Punjaban USA 🙌🙌❤️
Mandeep is from San Diego, California. Hailing from a farming family in a small village in Rajasthan, she defied odds as she embarked on the journey to become an air hostess right after high school. After Mandeep moved to the US 11 years ago, she underwent a complete career transformation and decided to pursue a nursing degree, ultimately achieving her nurse practitioner license and currently practicing in  inpatient and outpatient setting . She actively participates in medical bootcamps and finds joy in giving back by volunteering with underprivileged communities. Also, Mandeep is challenging gender norms by pursuing her passion for bodybuilding and training for competitions. Bodybuilding has given her a means to explore her athletic interests and enhance her mental wellbeing. Mandeep strongly believes that anything is possible with determination and a focused mindset.

💕Simran Khunkhun @lifeof__sim  was born in Ludhiana, Punjab, raised in Everett, Washington and lives in Temecula, California. 
💕Simran was born with a very rare heart defect called transposition of the great arteries. 
💕She had her first open heart surgery at the age of 3 in Boston. 
💕After 5 open heart surgeries and many heart attacks, she gets right back up! 
💕Simran has rescued many animals and continues to care for them. 
💕She loves to dance and was part of the Bhangra Team at North Carolina State University. Currently she’s a cosmologist and she’s pursing her degree in computer science! 
💕Her passion is to teach heart health awareness and goal is to show the younger generation to never give up and believe in yourself!
